inks in the entire photonics boom. \n\nSivers\u2019 high-power DFB laser arrays are built on $IQE Indium Phosphide wafers and form the critical light source inside Ayar Labs\u2019 SuperNova\u2122 modules. \n\nThese power Ayar Labs\u2019 TeraPHY\u2122 optical I/O chiplets - the co-packaged optics technology that is becoming essential for scaling hyperscale AI clusters, including Amazon\u2019s massive Trainium buildout. \n\nThe partnership with Ayar Labs was significantly expanded in December 2024 with NRE funding, pre-purchase agreements, and a clear focus on high-volume manufacturing readiness. Volume shipments are now expected to ramp hard through 2026 and 2027. \n\nAt the same time, Sivers secured a major SATCOM win with Intelsat, one of the world\u2019s largest satellite operators. In January 2025 they signed a contract to develop next-generation high-performance, low-cost digitizers based on the NXP Layerscape platform. \n\nMass production is scheduled to start in 2026 - another blue-chip revenue stream in the exploding satellite communications market. \n\nFrom the upstream AIXTRON -> IQE wafer supply all the way to powering $AMZN AWS Trainium AI infrastructure and Intelsat\u2019s SATCOM terminals, Sivers is quietly embedded in two of the fastest-growing megatrends in tech.\n\nUndervalued, de-risked, and heading straight into a dual volume inflection in AI photonics and SATCOM.", "source": "Twitter for iPhone", "retweetCount": 9, "replyCount": 2, "likeCount": 59, "quoteCount": 0, "viewCount": 5538, "createdAt": "Thu Apr 30 09:13:46 +0000 2026", "lang": "en", "bookmarkCount": 13, "isReply": false, "inReplyToId": null, "conversationId": "2049779232591458559", "displayTextRange": [0, 279], "inReplyToUserId": null, "inReplyToUsername": null, "author": {"type": "user", "userName": "PepInvestStocks", "url": "https://x.com/PepInvestStocks", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/PepInvestStocks", "id": "1463994727024545796", "name": "Pep Invest", "isVerified": false, "isBl